[[File:Kim, Anatoli.JPG|thumb|Anatoli Kim in 2013]] '''Anatoli Andreyevich Kim''' ({{lang-ru|Анато́лий Андре́евич Ким}}; born 15 June 1939) is a [[Russian language|Russian-language]] writer.<ref name="Bogdanova182">{{harvnb|Bogdanova|2005|p=182}}</ref>
==Background== Kim's father was a [[Koryo-saram|Soviet Korean]], the son of a man who immigrated to the [[Russian Far East]] in 1908; his mother was of Russian ethnicity. He claims to be a descendant of 15th-century Korean author [[Kim Si-seup]].<ref name="Sakhvesti">{{citation|url=http://www.sakhvesti.ru/?div=gubved&id=21914|title="Сахалин никогда не отпускал меня от себя…" (из бесед с писателем Анатолием Кимом)|date=2010-09-02|accessdate=2010-09-06|last=Egorova|first=Tatiana|periodical=Sakhalin-Kurile Information Agency}}</ref> He was born in Sergievka, [[Tulkibas District]], Chimkent Oblast, [[Kazakh Soviet Socialist Republic]] (today [[South Kazakhstan Province]], [[Kazakhstan]]) and spent his early years there.<ref name="Bogdanova182"/> In 1948, his family moved to the Russian Far East and [[Sakhalin]], where he lived until 1957 before entering an art school in [[Moscow]].<ref>{{harvnb|Choi|1988|p=63}}</ref>
==Translations== Aside from his original works, Kim has also translated a number of [[Kazakh language]] works into Russian, including [[Abdijamil Nurpeisov]]'s ''Last Duty'' (Последний долг) and [[Mukhtar Auezov]]'s ''Path of Abay'' (a re-translation, to replace an older Soviet-era version perceived as insufficient).<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.elmedia.kz/ru/?p=330 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722142302/http://www.elmedia.kz/ru/?p=330 |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2011-07-22 |periodical=Республика |title="Путь Абая": перечитывая заново |date=2009-03-17 |accessdate=2010-09-06 |first=Guljakhan |last=Otar }}</ref><ref>{{citation|first=Leonid|last=Terakpyan|title=Абдижамила Нурпеисова "Последний долг"|periodical=Октябрь|date=November 2001|url=http://magazines.russ.ru/october/2001/11/ter.html|accessdate=2010-09-06}}</ref>
==Selected works== *{{citation|title=Отец-лес: роман-притча|year=1989|publisher=Советский писатель|isbn=978-5-265-00994-4|oclc=21140793}}
