da]], handballer. * [[Shayne Gostisbehere]], ice hockey player. * [[Julen Guerrero]], footballer. * [[Lorena Guréndez]], rhythmic gymnast. * [[Imanol Harinordoquy]], rugby player.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/rugbyunion/international/france/2431544/France-look-to-Basque-prodigy.html |title=France look to Basque prodigy |first=Brendan |last=Gallagher |work=[[telegraph.co.uk]] |date=27 February 2002 |accessdate=14 July 2011 |quote=It's there in my heart, that's all that matters", Harinordoquy said. "I am French and Basque. There is no conflict, I am proud of both. . . . I have friends who are involved in the political side of things but that is not for me. My only interest is the culture, the Euskera language, the people, our history and ways.}}</ref> * [[Jimmie Heuga]], ski racer. * [[Raphaël Ibañez]], rugby player. * [[Miguel Indurain]],<ref name="trask35">Trask 1997, p. 35.</ref> cyclist. * [[Alberto Iñurrategi]], mountaineer. * [[José Ángel Iribar]], footballer. * [[Valeri Kharlamov]], ice hockey player. * [[Christophe Lamaison]], rugby player. * [[Tania Lamarca]], rhythmic gymnast. * [[Isidro Lángara]], footballer. * [[Jim Larranaga]], basketball coach * [[Luis María Lasúrtegui]] Berridi, rowing. * [[Marino Lejarreta]], cyclist. * [[Bixente Lizarazu]], footballer. * [[Fernando Llorente]], footballer. * [[Ryan Lochte]], swimmer. * [[Camille Lopez]], rugby player. * [[Juan Manuel López Iturriaga]], basketball player. * [[Estíbaliz Martínez]], rhythmic gymnast. * [[Javi Martínez]], footballer. * [[Juan Martínez de Irujo]], pelota player. * [[Iker Martínez de Lizarduy]], sailor. * [[Moncho Monsalve]], basketball coach. * [[Teresa Motos]], field hockey player. * [[Garbiñe Muguruza]], tennis player. * [[Juanito Oiarzabal]], mountaineer. * [[Leire Olaberria]], cyclist. * [[Abraham Olano]], cyclist. * [[Julio Olarticoechea]], footballer. * [[Aimar Olaizola]], pelota player. * [[José María Olazábal]], golfer.<ref name="trask35">Trask 1997, p. 35.</