'''Nick Tatham''' (born 11 June 1983, [[Hong Kong]]) is a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[singer-songwriter]] who has dealt with [[Tourette syndrome]] for most of his life whilst writing and recording [[ballads]], [[pop songs]] and other assorted modern music.<ref name="Digital Fix">Eamonn McCusker, [http://www.cdtimes.co.uk/content.php?contentid=636 Nick Tatham - Love Is All Around] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060309045315/http://www.cdtimes.co.uk/content.php?contentid=636 |date=9 March 2006 }}, The Digital Fix, 28 April 2004.</ref>
Tatham has appeared in several [[BBC]] television [[documentaries]]<ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b03bq4gy Inside Out South] BBC One - 23/09/2013</ref> and received the "Meridian Tonight Young Hero Award", live on TV in 2002, for his contributions to local music and his constant optimism and strength in dealing with his condition.<ref>TSA. [http://www.tsa-usa.org/kids/victories/Spring2001_victory.pdf Victories: Tatham (PDF)] {{full citation needed|date=April 2013}}</ref> In 2004 Tatham took the lead role in school student Richard Booth's ''Live for the Moment'', a film drama which chronicled the life of a person with Tourette's syndrome.<ref>[http://www.dorsetecho.co.uk/archive/2004/10/22/Dorset+Archive/5360788.Live_For_the_Moment__unclassified_/ Live for the Moment (unclassified)], Dorset Echo, 22 October 2004. Retrieved 2013-04-24.</ref>
On 20 April 2012 Tatham appeared in the blind auditions of the BBC talent series, ''[[The Voice UK|The Voice]]'', but failed to persuade any of the judging panel to choose him.<ref>Lisa McGarry, [http://www.unrealitytv.co.uk/the-voice/the-voice-2013-tourettes-sufferer-nick-tatham-chooses-the-wrong-song-fails-blind-audition/ The Voice 2013: Tourette’s sufferer Nick Tatham chooses the wrong song & fails blind audition!], UnrealityTV, 20 April 2013.</ref>
